dgxarley: bake a DeepSeek-V4-Flash FlashMLA sparse-decode kernel for sm_121a
into the standard sm121 image.

V4's attention backend (deepseek_v4_backend.py) does a hard `import flash_mla` +
`flash_mla.flash_mla_with_kvcache(...)` with NO fallback path, and upstream
FlashMLA ships no sm_120/sm_121 sparse-decode kernel — so DeepSeek-V4-Flash-FP8
otherwise dies at the first forward with `ModuleNotFoundError: flash_mla` or
`Unsupported architecture for sparse decode fwd`. See UPSTREAM_DSV4_BUGS.md §7,
SGLang #23657, DeepGEMM #317.

This installs stock flash_mla (the wrapper WRAPS its interface; flash_mla
provides flash_mla_interface + FlashMLASchedMeta + host-side get_mla_metadata)
and builds 0xSero/deepseek-v4-flash-sm120's `deepseek_v4_kernel` CUDA extension
retargeted from sm_120a to DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH (sm_121a = GB10), then drops its
top-level sitecustomize hook into dist-packages so every forked sglang worker
monkey-patches flash_mla_with_kvcache before the first model forward. The hook
only takes over the sparse-FP8-decode path on sm12x and otherwise falls through
to stock flash_mla, so it is inert for non-V4 models.

flash_mla is cloned + checked out + submodule-init'd explicitly (NOT
`pip install git+`): FlashMLA's setup.py needs the csrc/cutlass git submodule,
which a `git+` install does not reliably fetch. Its sm90/sm100 kernels
cross-compile fine on CUDA 13.2 (they never RUN on sm121 — the 0xSero kernel
replaces decode); MAX_JOBS/NVCC_THREADS are bounded to 8 so the heavy CUTLASS
build does not OOM the GB10 builder. The 0xSero kernel is built in ONE step
(pip install with DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH set) — a separate build_ext + pip install
would rebuild it with the sm_120a default and clobber the sm_121a .so.

Placed AFTER the `uv pip install ./python` step and BEFORE the directory split,
so the kernel + flash_mla + sitecustomize.py land in dist-packages and propagate
to the runtime stage via the existing COPY --from=builder dist-packages-N steps.

FATAL: a build failure (flash_mla won't install / kernel won't compile) aborts
the whole image build — we do NOT ship a standard image that silently lacks
V4-Flash support. To opt out, clear DSV4_KERNEL_REPO in the recipe.

Gated on DSV4_KERNEL_REPO being non-empty (recipe sets it) — empty = skip.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly AFTER dockerfile-sm121.patch
and dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -296,6 +296,38 @@ RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
 RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
     uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python

+# dgxarley: DeepSeek-V4-Flash FlashMLA sparse-decode kernel for sm_121a (GB10).
+# Stock flash_mla (interface + host get_mla_metadata; the 0xSero wrapper wraps
+# it) + the 0xSero sm_120 sparse-decode extension retargeted to DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH.
+# Drops a sitecustomize hook into dist-packages so every forked sglang worker
+# patches flash_mla_with_kvcache before the first forward. Installed BEFORE the
+# directory split so it propagates to the runtime stage. FATAL on failure (clear
+# DSV4_KERNEL_REPO in the recipe to opt out). See UPSTREAM_DSV4_BUGS.md §7.
+ARG FLASH_MLA_REPO=""
+ARG FLASH_MLA_REF=""
+ARG DSV4_KERNEL_REPO=""
+ARG DSV4_KERNEL_REF="main"
+ARG DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH=""
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    if [ -n "$DSV4_KERNEL_REPO" ]; then \
+      ( set -e; \
+        echo "=== dgxarley DSV4 FlashMLA: flash_mla@${FLASH_MLA_REF}, kernel ${DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH} ==="; \
+        if [ -n "$FLASH_MLA_REF" ]; then \
+          git clone "${FLASH_MLA_REPO}" /tmp/flashmla; \
+          git -C /tmp/flashmla checkout "${FLASH_MLA_REF}"; \
+          git -C /tmp/flashmla submodule update --init --recursive csrc/cutlass; \
+          MAX_JOBS=8 NVCC_THREADS=8 uv pip install --no-deps --no-build-isolation /tmp/flashmla; \
+          rm -rf /tmp/flashmla; \
+        fi; \
+        git clone "${DSV4_KERNEL_REPO}" /tmp/dsv4; \
+        git -C /tmp/dsv4 checkout "${DSV4_KERNEL_REF}"; \
+        DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH="${DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH}" NVCC_THREADS=8 MAX_JOBS=8 uv pip install --no-deps --no-build-isolation /tmp/dsv4; \
+        cp /tmp/dsv4/deepseek_v4_kernel/sitecustomize_hook.py /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/sitecustomize.py; \
+        rm -rf /tmp/dsv4 ); \
+    else \
+      echo "=== Skipping DSV4 FlashMLA kernel (DSV4_KERNEL_REPO empty) ==="; \
+    fi
+
 # Break up dist-packages into smaller layers to avoid hitting Docker layer size limits
 COPY stages/directory_split2.sh /opt/directory_split2.sh
 RUN chmod +x /opt/directory_split2.sh && \
